<!-- pattern: not-applicable — launchd LaunchAgent unit mirroring com.minsky.tick-loop.plist; the OTP transient-restart Supervisor semantics (Armstrong 2007) are already declared at vision.md § "Pattern conformance index" for the supervisor unit-files, this is just the runany unit the supervisor topology covers. -->
<!--
Minsky run-anywhere conductor — launchd LaunchAgent for macOS.

Task: `runany-self-restart-bounded-timelimit` (TASKS.md P0). The OS half
of a two-layer supervisor (rule #1 — compose, don't duplicate):

  - launchd KeepAlive{SuccessfulExit:false} = OTP "transient" restart
    (Armstrong 2007): respawn ONLY on non-zero exit. The conductor's
    clean exit 0 at MINSKY_RUN_TIME_LIMIT is therefore a true terminal
    stop — launchd does NOT bring it back (Acceptance #3: 0 restarts
    after the deadline).
  - ThrottleInterval is a single FLAT floor (5s) — launchd cannot
    escalate. The escalating, capped, reset-on-sustained-health backoff
    lives in the conductor's in-process startup self-throttle
    (decideStartupThrottle, scripts/restart-supervisor.mjs; wired in
    scripts/orchestrate.mjs), which reads its own persisted crash
    history at boot. ThrottleInterval is just the minimum gap launchd
    enforces between respawns; the conductor adds the rest on top.

Placeholders substituted by setup.sh via envsubst:
  ${MINSKY_HOME}   — absolute path to the minsky repo checkout

Note on filename: this is a template (it carries the ${MINSKY_HOME}
envsubst placeholder, same as the other com.minsky.*.plist units) but is
named `.plist` not `.plist.tmpl` so setup.sh's Darwin `*.plist` glob
(setup.sh:409) renders + bootstraps it; a `.tmpl` suffix would make it
inert. See docs/run-anywhere.md.

Install (handled by `pnpm minsky:setup` / setup.sh):
  launchctl bootstrap gui/$(id -u) ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.minsky.runany.plist
  launchctl enable gui/$(id -u)/com.minsky.runany
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.minsky.runany</string>

    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}</string>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>MINSKY_HOME</key>
        <string>${MINSKY_HOME}</string>
        <!-- Hard wall-clock ceiling (rule #6 — stay alive, but bounded).
             At this elapsed time (measured against the persisted
             supervised-run origin, carried across launchd restarts) the
             conductor stops scheduling, drains, and exits 0 cleanly;
             KeepAlive{SuccessfulExit:false} then does NOT respawn it.
             Accepts `<n>s|m|h`; default 10h is applied by
             scripts/restart-supervisor.mjs when this is unset/typo'd
             (rule #7 graceful degrade). Lower it for a bounded soak. -->
        <key>MINSKY_RUN_TIME_LIMIT</key>
        <string>10h</string>
    </dict>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/bin/bash</string>
        <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/distribution/systemd/run-runany.sh</string>
    </array>

    <!-- Restart only on non-zero exit (transient policy, Armstrong 2007).
         The deadline-driven clean exit 0 is intentionally NOT respawned. -->
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <dict>
        <key>SuccessfulExit</key>
        <false/>
    </dict>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Flat minimum gap between respawns; the escalating backoff is the
         conductor's in-process self-throttle, not this number. -->
    <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
    <integer>5</integer>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/.minsky/runany.out.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/.minsky/runany.err.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
